text: :For another frog called the lanceback tree frog, see Scinax duartei. The lanceback tree frog (Scinax curicica) is a frog. It lives in Minas Gerais in Brazil. This frog is brown or gray in color. It has a mark between its eyes. It has two stripes down its back. The insides of its back legs are bright yellow. Scientists used to think this was the same frog as Scinax duartei. ==References== Category:Frogs of South America
title: Scinax curicica
